# Preamble

The following analysis is a report on the activity, quality and data contained in the [PROKPATH registry](https://sites.google.com/ebma.com.au/prokpath-registry/home).

Analysis packages were loaded initially into the *R* environment.



::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
package 'xfun' successfully unpacked and MD5 sums checked
```


:::

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
package 'litedown' successfully unpacked and MD5 sums checked

The downloaded binary packages are in
	C:\Users\cscho\AppData\Local\Temp\Rtmp2pUSyD\downloaded_packages
```


:::
:::



Access to the PROKPATH datasets was pre-authorised.



::: {.cell}

:::



A function was generated to retrieve files using the *googledrive* package, to call on later in the analysis for processing data imports.



::: {.cell}

:::

::: {.cell}

:::



Data was retrieved from live database tables. Source files were specified and stored as global variables to call on in further functions.



::: {.cell}

:::

::: {.cell}

:::



A static registry snapshot was retrieved and formatted based on the fixed date of preparation of the snapshot (31-Mar-2025).



::: {.cell}

:::

::: {.cell}

:::



# Context

# Recruitment Flow by Region

Flowcharts as per STROBE [@Vandenbroucke2007] and RECORD [@Benchimol2015] guidelines were generated for each region (shoulder, hip, knee) enrolled into the Registry. Followup was set to eligibility at 12months.



::: {.cell}

:::

::: {.cell}

:::

::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![Flowchart of extraction and followup of surgical sample from the Registry - 1](PROKPATHGov_files/figure-html/fig-strobe-cohort1-1.png){#fig-strobe-cohort1 width=672}
:::
:::

::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![Flowchart of extraction and followup of surgical sample from the Registry - 2](PROKPATHGov_files/figure-html/fig-strobe-cohort2-1.png){#fig-strobe-cohort2 width=672}
:::
:::



Cumulative recruitment over time was plotted from Registry inception to the present.



::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![Cumulative record creation within SHARKS from inception to present](PROKPATHGov_files/figure-html/fig-progress-1.png){#fig-progress width=672}
:::
:::



# Missingness and Compliance

## Baseline and Intraoperative



::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![Missingness of baseline PROMs and intraoperative date by registry cohort](PROKPATHGov_files/figure-html/fig-baseline-miss-1.png){#fig-baseline-miss width=672}
:::
:::



Missingness for baseline PROMs (represented by VR12) and intraoperative data is captured in @fig-baseline-miss. Intraoperative data was captured slightly differently between cohorts in the previous system, so multiple fields have been utilised to illustrate intraoperative capture across cohorts.

Overall, there are variable response rates for baseline scores across cohorts. This may reflect variable engagement during consultant clinics. We have also identified a system issue that is impeding scores from being sent to patients that are being re-categorised from one cohort to another. This is predominantly affecting cases that have limited information on their referral and are subsequently moved from the *General* cohort.

## Patient-reported Outcomes by TimePoint



::: {.cell}

:::

::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![Missingness of SANE by Timepoint across all cohorts](PROKPATHGov_files/figure-html/fig-sane-miss-1.png){#fig-sane-miss width=672}
:::
:::

::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![Missingness of SANE for surgical cases by Timepoint across all cohorts](PROKPATHGov_files/figure-html/fig-sane2-miss-1.png){#fig-sane2-miss width=672}
:::
:::

::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![Missingness of KOOS JR by Timepoint in the Knee Arthritis cohort](PROKPATHGov_files/figure-html/fig-kneearthritis-miss-1.png){#fig-kneearthritis-miss width=672}
:::
:::

::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![Missingness of IKDC2000 Score by Timepoint in the Tibiofemoral Instability cohort](PROKPATHGov_files/figure-html/fig-tfi-miss-1.png){#fig-tfi-miss width=672}
:::
:::

::: {.cell}

:::



The cumulative results of the Registry illustrate difficulty in engaging patients beyond short term followup.

## Baseline by Year



::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![Missingness of Baseline Oxford Knee Score by Year in the Knee Arthritis cohort](PROKPATHGov_files/figure-html/fig-ka-missbase-1.png){#fig-ka-missbase width=672}
:::
:::

::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![Missingness of Baseline IKDC2000 by Year in the Tibiofemoral Instability cohort](PROKPATHGov_files/figure-html/fig-tfi-missbase-1.png){#fig-tfi-missbase width=672}
:::
:::



The results displayed in @fig-tfi-missbase helped to identify the system issue preventing cohort-specific scores being resent to cases that were transferred from one cohort to another. This has now been rectified and eligible cases have been resent links to complete the required questionnaires.

# Cohort Analysis

The VR12 is a *general* health questionnaire that is presented to *all* patients enrolled in the registry.



::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![Summary of VR12-PCS at baseline by cohort](PROKPATHGov_files/figure-html/fig-vr12pcs-cohort-1.png){#fig-vr12pcs-cohort width=672}
:::
:::

::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![Summary of VR12-MCS at baseline by cohort](PROKPATHGov_files/figure-html/fig-vr12mcs-cohort-1.png){#fig-vr12mcs-cohort width=672}
:::
:::



Between-cohort variability is observed for the Physical Component Score of the VR12, but not as pronounced for the Mental Component Score. Most notable is the high variation within all cohorts for both VR12 component scores.



::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![Summary of SANE by Timepoint](PROKPATHGov_files/figure-html/fig-sane-1.png){#fig-sane width=672}
:::
:::

::: {.cell}

:::

::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![Satisfaction with symptom relief by Time Point and Cohort captured by post-operative MODEMs](PROKPATHGov_files/figure-html/fig-modemp1-1.png){#fig-modemp1 width=672}
:::
:::

::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![Expectations of symptom relief by Cohort and Treatment TYpe captured by pre-treatment MODEMs](PROKPATHGov_files/figure-html/fig-modempre1-1.png){#fig-modempre1 width=672}
:::
:::

::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![Satisfaction with sleep comfort by Time Point and Cohort captured by post-operative MODEMs](PROKPATHGov_files/figure-html/fig-modemp3-1.png){#fig-modemp3 width=672}
:::
:::



